'''Kuruma Ōtoshi Shrine''' (車大歳神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in the Kuruma district of [[Suma Ward]], [[Kobe City]], [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]]. Currently, it does not have a resident priest; the chief priest of [[Gion Shrine]] in Kamigion-chō, [[Hyōgo Ward]], oversees its administration.
== deity == * [[Toshigami|Ōtoshi Mioya no Kami]] (大歳御祖神)
== History == While the origins of the shrine are unclear, ''Mukogun-shi'' records its founding in the second year of [[Taika]] (646). It is also said to have been relocated from Nyūgo, [[Yabe District]], [[Settsu Province]], in [[:en:Ōei|Ōei]] 4 (1397).
